    "name": "Mesh Independence Study — CFD Hemolysis Model",
    "description": "A structured mesh independence study was conducted across three refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. The study examined convergence of wall shear stress distributions and scalar stress fields relevant to hemolysis prediction. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI) for each operating point.",
